    "encrypted": "false",
    "title": "Bringing Computer Systems to the Classroom",
    "long_instructions": "<div style=\"background-color: #026C7A; color: #FFFFFF; padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px; width: 90%; margin: 20px auto;\">\r\n    \r\n<p style=\"font-size: 44pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; text-align: center;margin-top: 15px;\">🎉🎉🎉</p><br>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 24pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; text-align: center; margin-top: 15px;\">Congratulations!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 10px;text-align: center;\">\r\n        You've finished the second lesson in this professional learning module! <br> Data in Computer Systems is up next! \r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"15\">\r\n    <tr>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #b2dee3; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson One</b><br>Teaching Computer<br>Systems & Devices</td>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #b2dee3; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson Two</b><br>Hardware, Software  <br> & Operating Systems</td>\r\n        <td style=\"background-color: #f7f8fa; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson Three</b><br>Data in<br> Computer Systems</td>\r\n          <td style=\"background-color: #f7f8fa; text-align: center;\"><b>Lesson Four</b><br>Preparing for<br>the Final Project</td>\r\n        \r\n</table>\r\n\r\n#### **Reflecting on teaching about computer systems:**\r\n \r\n- #### Which topics (troubleshooting, optimization, system performance) might be the most challenging for students, and how can you support their understanding?\r\n\r\n- #### How can you incorporate AI chatbots effectively to help students troubleshoot system issues while ensuring they critically evaluate the responses?\r\n\r\n- #### What strategies will you use to help students connect hardware and software concepts to real-world applications?\r\n\r\n#### *These questions are just starting points for reflection and discussion—there’s no need to answer all of them. Focus on the ones that resonate most with your teaching experience and goals.*\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: left; margin:20px 0px 30px 0px\">\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/teaching-ai-and-the-systems-that-power-it-pl-reflection-teaching-about-computer-systems/40996?u=amanda.dennard1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/7dbe63a051fbad4ef262d6ab710e2966-image-1731959037460.png\" style=\"width: auto; height: 100px;\"  alt=\"A browser with two text boxes, both including an avatar and lines of text.\"></a>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #007786; border-radius: 20px 20px 20px 20px; color: #000000; width: 80%; margin-left: 5%; margin-right: 5%; padding: 10px 10px 5px 10px;\">\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Post to the Code.org Forum</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.2; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\">Share your response and read other educators' ideas on the forum! Click on the icon to the left to direct to our forum post.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n",
